%N A209491 Table T(n,d), read by antidiagonals, gives the number of subsets of length n containing an arithmetic progression of length 3 with distance d.
%C A209491 n offset is 3, d offset is 1, so 1st term is T(3,1).
%F A209491 T(n,d) = 2^n - prod_{1=0 to d-1} Tri(floor((n + i)/d) + 2) where Tri(n) is the n-th tribonacci number.
%e A209491 Table begins:
